    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Boil a full kettle</p><p>Peel (scrape the skin off with a teaspoon) and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>ginger</strong></p><p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Add the <strong>chopped ginger</strong> and<strong> chopped garlic</strong> to a heat-proof bowl with your <strong>cayenne</strong> <strong>pepper</strong> (can't handle the heat? Go easy!)</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/spicy-sichuan-style-pork-noodle-bowl/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp] </span><strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a medium high heat</p><p>Add your<strong> toasted sesame oil </strong>and heat for 1-2 min or until very hot, then carefully pour the <strong>heated toasted sesame oil </strong>into the bowl,<strong> </strong>give it a good mix up and set aside for later (save the pan!) \u2013 this is your <strong>chilli oil</strong></p><p>Tip: Be careful \u2013 the garlic and ginger will sizzle from the heat of the oil!</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/spicy-sichuan-style-pork-noodle-bowl/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Return the pan to a high heat with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong></p><p>Once hot, add your<strong> mince </strong>(remove the paper if required!) and cook for 3-4 min or until caramelised, breaking it up with a wooden spoon as you go</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/spicy-sichuan-style-pork-noodle-bowl/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Top, tail and grate your <strong>carrot[s]</strong> (no need to peel!)</p><p>Trim, then slice your<strong> sweet pea pods</strong> finely on a diagonal</p><p>Trim, then slice your <strong>spring onion[s] </strong>finely</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/spicy-sichuan-style-pork-noodle-bowl/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>medium egg noodles</strong> to a pot and cover them with<strong> boiled water</strong> until fully submerged</p><p>Bring to the boil over a high heat and cook for 5-6 min or until cooked with a slight bite</p><p>Once done, drain, reserving a cup of <strong>starchy noodle water</strong> and set aside</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/spicy-sichuan-style-pork-noodle-bowl/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add <strong>half</strong> your <strong>soy sauce</strong> (save the rest for later!) to the <strong>browned mince </strong>and the <strong>sliced sweet pea pods </strong>and cook for 4 min further or until the <strong>mince </strong>is cooked through (no pink meat!) \u2013 this is your <strong>soy mince & sweet pea pods</strong></p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/spicy-sichuan-style-pork-noodle-bowl/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>remaining soy sauce</strong>, <strong>rice vinegar </strong>and <strong>peanut butter </strong>to the <strong>chilli oil </strong>with a pinch of <strong>sugar</strong> and a good grind of <strong>black pepper</strong> and give everything a good mix up \u2013 this is your<strong> sauce</strong></p><p>Once the noodles are done, add a splash of the<strong> starchy noodle water</strong> to the <strong>sauce</strong> \u2013 this is your <strong>Sichuan-style chilli sauce</strong></p><p>Tip: You want the sauce to be a single cream consistency so it can coat all of the noodles!</p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/spicy-sichuan-style-pork-noodle-bowl/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>Sichuan-style chilli sauce</strong> to the bottom of your serving bowl[s]</p><p>Serve the <strong>drained noodles</strong> on top with the <strong>soy mince & sweet pea pods</strong> and <strong>grated carrot</strong></p><p>Garnish with the <strong>sliced spring onion</strong></p><p>To eat, toss the noodles and veg through the Sichuan-style chilli sauce</p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
